size":"small"},{"#text":"https://lastfm.freetls.fastly.net/i/u/64s/2a96cbd8b46e442fc41c2b86b821562f.png","size":"medium"},{"#text":"https://lastfm.freetls.fastly.net/i/u/174s/2a96cbd8b46e442fc41c2b86b821562f.png","size":"large"},{"#text":"https://lastfm.freetls.fastly.net/i/u/300x300/2a96cbd8b46e442fc41c2b86b821562f.png","size":"extralarge"},{"#text":"https://lastfm.freetls.fastly.net/i/u/300x300/2a96cbd8b46e442fc41c2b86b821562f.png","size":"mega"},{"#text":"https://lastfm.freetls.fastly.net/i/u/300x300/2a96cbd8b46e442fc41c2b86b821562f.png","size":""}]}]},"tags":{"tag":[{"name":"House","url":"https://www.last.fm/tag/House"},{"name":"electronic","url":"https://www.last.fm/tag/electronic"},{"name":"techno","url":"https://www.last.fm/tag/techno"},{"name":"electro house","url":"https://www.last.fm/tag/electro+house"},{"name":"electro","url":"https://www.last.fm/tag/electro"}]},"bio":{"links":{"link":{"#text":"","rel":"original","href":"https://last.fm/music/Joachim+Garraud/+wiki"}},"published":"30 May 2006, 19:51","summary":"Joachim Garraud (born in 1968 at Nantes) is a french DJ. Producer and remixer of David Guetta, Geyster, Paul Johnson, Deep Dish, David Bowie, OMD, Kylie Minogue, Mylene Farmer, Cassius, Belamour, Kid Vicious and Saffron Hill, he is an essential actor of the european House scene. He is also co-fondator of Gum Prod, Square Prod and Gum Records. \n\nOne of his particularity who made his fame is to mix sound and video in same time in live with a Pioneer DVJX1 Professional DVD Turntable. <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/Joachim+Garraud\">Read more on Last.fm</a>","content":"Joachim Garraud (born in 1968 at Nantes) is a french DJ. Producer and remixer of David Guetta, Geyster, Paul Johnson, Deep Dish, David Bowie, OMD, Kylie Minogue, Mylene Farmer, Cassius, Belamour, Kid Vicious and Saffron Hill, he is an essential actor of the european House scene. He is also co-fondator of Gum Prod, Square Prod and Gum Records. \n\nOne of his particularity who made his fame is to mix sound and video in same time in live with a Pioneer DVJX1 Professional DVD Turntable. His podcast \"Zemixx\" is one of the most downloaded of Itunes Store, ranked #1 many times in 2006.  <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/Joachim+Garraud\">Read more on Last.fm</a>. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply."}}}